# Raw Data Access Guide

## Datasets

### Amsterdam (ODiN 2023)
- **Source**: Statistics Netherlands (CBS)
- **File**: `odin_2023_commuting_amsterdam.parquet` (~250 MB)
- **Access**: 
  - Direct download from CBS Databank: https://www.cbs.nl/en-gb/our-services/customised-research/odeurbaancijfers
  - Or: Pre-processed version available via Zenodo (DOI: [insert DOI when uploaded])
- **Rows**: 681 commuting trips
- **Columns**: 200+ (see `../data_documentation/amsterdam_variables.md`)

### London (NTS 2023)
- **Source**: UK Data Archive (NTS Study 5340)
- **File**: `nts_2023_commuting_london.parquet` (~320 MB)
- **Access**:
  - UK Data Archive: https://beta.ukdataservice.ac.uk/datacatalogue/series/5340
  - Username/password required (institutional access)
  - Pre-processed version: Zenodo DOI [insert]
- **Rows**: 25,188 commuting trips
- **Columns**: 170+ (see `../data_documentation/london_variables.md`)

## Setup Instructions

### Step 1: Download Raw Data
```bash
# Create raw data folder
mkdir -p src/raw

# Option 1a: Download from CBS (Amsterdam)
# Visit CBS portal, download ODiN 2023, save as:
# src/raw/odin_2023_commuting_amsterdam.csv

# Option 1b: Use Zenodo link (if examiner has no CBS access)
wget https://zenodo.org/record/[record-id]/files/odin_2023_commuting_amsterdam.parquet \
  -O src/raw/odin_2023_commuting_amsterdam.parquet

# Option 2: Download from UK Data Archive (London)
# Requires registration. Download NTS 2023, save as:
# src/raw/nts_2023_commuting_london.csv
```

### Step 2: Validate Data Integrity

jupyter notebooks phase1_amsterdam_dataload.ipynb 
and
jupyter noteboks phase2_london_dataload.ipynb

Script will check:
- File exists ✓
- Row counts match expected (681, 25,188)
- No corrupted records
- Column presence

